## Data Flow

### End-to-End Flow Diagram

```
┌──────────────┐
│   Client     │
└──────┬───────┘
       │ 1. HTTP POST Request
       ↓
┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
│  NotificationApiController           │
│  - Validates DTO                     │
│  - Checks async flag                 │
└──────┬───────────────────────────────┘
       │ 2. Call service method
       ↓
┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
│  NotificationService                 │
│  - Determines notification type      │
│  - Builds email content              │
│  - Calls provider                    │
└──────┬───────────────────────────────┘
       │ 3. Send email
       ↓
┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
│  EmailNotificationProvider           │
│  - Creates MimeMessage               │
│  - Adds attachments                  │
│  - Retry logic (max 3 attempts)      │
└──────┬───────────────────────────────┘
       │ 4. SMTP Send
       ↓
┌──────────────────────────────────────┐
│  SMTP Server (Gmail/SendGrid/etc)    │
└──────┬───────────────────────────────┘
       │ 5. Email delivered
       ↓
┌──────────────┐
│  Recipient   │
└──────────────┘
```

### Detailed Flow Steps

#### Step 1: API Request
```json
POST /sourceintelligence-service/api/v1/notifications/send
{
  "notificationType": "EMAIL",
  "async": true,
  "emailNotification": {
    "to": ["user@example.com"],
    "subject": "Test Email",
    "body": "Hello World",
    "htmlContent": false
  }
}
```

#### Step 2: Validation
- DTO validation using Jakarta Bean Validation
- Email format validation
- Required field checks

#### Step 3: Service Processing
- Async/sync decision based on `async` flag
- Email content preparation
- Metadata handling

#### Step 4: Email Sending
- MimeMessage creation
- Attachment processing
- SMTP transmission with retry

#### Step 5: Response
```json
{
  "status": "SUCCESS",
  "message": "Notification sent successfully",
  "notificationId": "uuid-123",
  "sentAt": "2026-05-05T10:30:00Z",
  "recipientCount": 1
}
```

